      <notesStmt>
        <note>Title from cover page (f. 1r) and f. 15v. Cover page reads: atha śarabhasahasranāmaprārambhaḥ. F. 15v reads: iti śarabhasahasranāmasampūrṇaṁ. Title from colophon is Śarabheśvarasahasranāman. F. 15v reads: iti śarabhasahasranāmasampūrṇaṁ.</note>
        <note>Title of this text, according to New Cat. Cat., is Śarabha(īśvara)sahasranāma(-stava, stotra).</note>
        <note>Copied by Dhoṇḍabhaṭṭa.</note>
        <note>Written 9 lines per leaf.</note>
        <note>Good condition. Mistakes marked over in black.</note>
        <note>Begins: śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ śrīsarasvatyai namaḥ śrīgurubyāṁ namaḥ hariḥ om̐ śrī devyuvāca devadevamahādeva bhaktānugrahakārakaḥ durllabhā śārabhī vidyā guhyād guhyatarāparā (verse 1). guṭikā pādukā siddhistathā siddhiśca khecarī śāpānugrahasāmrthyā parakāyapraveśane (verse 2).</note>
        <note>Stotra begins f. 3r: atha sahasranāmaprārambhaḥ om̐ śrīṁ śrīṁ siddhīśvaraḥ sākṣāt kheṁ kheṁ garvāpahārakaḥ hrīṁ hrīṁ spreṁ sphreṁ [hlauṁ hlauṁ?] 'lū 'lūṁ pakṣirājaḥ pratāpavān (verse 1).</note>
        <note>Ends: svamātṛyonivad goyyaṁ vidyaiṣetyāgamājaguḥ paṭhanīyam idaṁ nityaṁ ātmanā śreyam ichatā na muñcati gṛhaṁ tas[m]āllakṣmī vāṇī sadaiva hi (verse 128).</note>
      </notesStmt>
